  "commentary": "With SPX at 6833.24 sitting below the GEX flip at 6842, dealers are in positive gamma territory and will be selling into any rallies toward the massive 6840-6850 resistance zone where 24.4B and 23.4B in positive gamma create strong hedging headwinds. The recent wall break and GEX surge events suggest we just saw significant options flow that's now creating this heavy positive gamma ceiling above current levels. Watch for mean reversion behavior with dealers providing liquidity - they'll buy any dips toward 6820-6825 negative gamma zone and aggressively sell rallies approaching 6840-6850.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned between 6820 and 6840 with upside capped by heavy dealer selling.",
